The code is structured clearly and logically, with responsibilities separated where reasonable.

Any UX/UI adjustments needed for the feature are designed thoughtfully and documented briefly.

The new functionality works as intended during normal use.

Existing tests still pass, and new functionality is covered by at least basic tests.

The project builds without ESLint errors.

Important parts of the code are documented using TSDoc where relevant.

Technical documentation is written in English and understandable for teammates.

The work is committed and pushed to GitLab, following version control and coding conventions used in the project.